AttributeList.Text: The sequence is initiated via the interface signals ..afl
Message 17 - Sequence Not Held To abort or continue the clean it must have already been held.
Message 21 - Line Sterilising *** Use Sterilising Seq running bit ***
Message 22 - Inhibited by Running Sequence *** Use Production Seq running bit ***

Reset all CIP commands except START. On a new non-zero error message being displayed reset all commands from SCADA so they take no action. Also, start a delay off timer to cancel display of the error message.

Set sequence hold if sequence is running and a hold fault condition is detected or a sequence hold command is received from SCADA.
When a validated CONTINUE command is received from SCADA and all fault conditions are cleared then reset sequence hold.
Added "Product Request" (CIP Complete) to prevent sequence going into hold when Central CIP completes
Reset when circuit not running i.e after an abort.
Reset sequnece to step 0 and clear down step value and dimension words.
Dev Check following Route valves Open - 09.10, 09.08, 09.45, 10.21, 10.23, 10.25 and following Route Valves closed - 09.09, 09.05, 10.24
Check Condenstate OK, then Set CIP Route Open
Cycle 2 + T69 (2 Secs) to Cycle 3 Delay Timer.
Product_Request means "CIP Complete" in this context.
Check following valve are open V09.11, V10.25, V10.27, V10.83
The next step number is different to the current step then set flag.
Current step value decremented to zero
With count enabled and timer not held count down on each 1 second pulse.
On detection of a new step, the timer is reset to 0 and will then start timing whilst on the current step.
